search::searchStringToArray()

Description
    private array search::searchStringToArray(string $searchStr)

Parameters
    searchStr
    A string value to convert to an array.

Return Values
    An array, $keywords, created from the string, $searchStr.

Examples
    <?php
	...
	$keywords = array();
	$fullSearchStr = NULL;
	for($i = 0; $i < $this->searchRows; $i++) {
	    if(!isset($searchString[$i]) || is_empty($searchString[$i])) {
		continue;
	    }
	
            if(isset($bool[$i]) && !is_empty($bool[$i])) {
	        $fullSearchStr .= " " . $bool[$i];
	    }

 	    $fullSearchStr .= " " . $searchString[$i] . "";
	}
	
	$keywords = $this->searchStringToArray($fullSearchStr);
	...
    ?>

See Also
    search::createSearchArray()
